Rating: 4
I have made this dish multiple times, including for dinner parties as it is easy to do all the prep work ahead of time. The recipe is excellent just as written, but I have modified it at times with great success as well. Adding a bit of lemon zest and capers helps to give it more of a Mediterranean flavor and brightness. I typically will add a full cup of wine too rather than just 3/4. I have served it over French bread as recommended, as well as rice cooked in broth and pasta as well. Also, substituting halibut works well as it is very thick and flaky and holds up well to the sauce. Herbs such as Herb de Provence or thyme are nice additions too, especially if you have the herbs fresh in the garden and are looking for a good use for them. Definitely try - you won't be disappointed!

