Rating: 4
The recipe was a delicious surprise. I expected it to be a little more bland. I used a west coast fish, white sea bass, instead of the typical Chilean sea bass and a chardonnay. I also added a little extra red pepper (3/4 tsp total) and a few extra anchovy fillets. Instead of regular French bread, I substituted whole wheat French bread which added extra flavor. Use good quality olive oil on the toasted bread as it adds a surprising amount of flavor. The recommendation of four slices of bread (for 4-8 ounce fish steaks)was less than adequate to have bread with each piece of fish. Make 7-8 slices and serve each piece of fish on the bread like an open face sandwich. That way you get the flavor of the bread/oil with each bite of fish. I will definitely make this one again.

